This article is a fact sheet from the White House on their investments in clean energy. President Obama met with clean energy entrepreneurs and research leaders to discuss his strategy for building a clean energy economy and creating jobs. The American Reinvestment Recovery Act and the FY10 budget increase investment in research, clean energy technologies, and incentives for private sector R&D. The ARRA includes $39 billion in energy investments at the Department of Energy and $20 billion in tax incentives for clean energy. The President's budget also proposes $75 billion to make the Research and Experimentation Tax Credit permanent. The article highlights some technologies that are part of the program, such as the Apollo Light Pipe and Solyndra Solar Panel. The article also mentions the success story of Serious Materials, a leading energy-saving building materials company that is hiring workers and reopening plants.